OL,3,CWhy did Labour U-turn on its #28bn
OL,4,Cgreen spending plan?
OL,6,FBut last year, Labour adjusted the
OL,7,Fplan to say the #28 billion-a-year
OL,8,Ftarget would likely be met in the
OL,9,Fsecond half of a first parliament,
OL,10,Frather than immediately, if the party
OL,11,Fwins the next election.
OL,13,FThere has been growing confusion over
OL,14,Fthe status of the target in recent
OL,15,Fweeks, with Ms Reeves repeatedly
OL,16,Fdeclining to recommit to the spending
OL,17,Fpledge, while Sir Keir said earlier
OL,18,Fthis week it was "desperately needed"
OL,19,Fto achieve a fully clean power grid by
OL,20,F2030.
