OL,3,CWhy did Labour U-turn on its #28bn
OL,4,Cgreen spending plan?
OL,6,FThere is a scaled-down commitment to
OL,7,Fupgrade five million energy
OL,8,Finefficient homes over the next
OL,9,Fparliament, and Labour says it is
OL,10,Fdoubling the government's #6.6 billion
OL,11,Ffor insulation and clean heating with
OL,12,Fanother #6.6 billion pledge.
OL,14,FThe party also says it would introduce
OL,15,Fa "proper" windfall tax on oil and gas
OL,16,Fcompanies which would raise #10.8
OL,17,Fbillion over five years to help pay
OL,18,Ffor its plans.
OL,20,FWhy did Labour abandon its flagship
OL,21,Fspending plan?
