OL,3,CWhy did Labour U-turn on its #28bn
OL,4,Cgreen spending plan?
OL,6,FBut the #28 billion pledge also opened
OL,7,Fup an attack line for the Tories, who
OL,8,Fare languishing far behind in the
OL,9,Fpolls in an election year and said
OL,10,FLabour would have to raise taxes to
OL,11,Fpay for an "unfunded spending spree".
OL,13,FThe Conservatives also attacked the
OL,14,Fpledge to insulate 19 million homes,
OL,15,Fclaiming Treasury costing had
OL,16,Fsuggested it would cost double the #6
OL,17,Fbillion estimate.
OL,19,FWill dropping the pledge make the row
OL,20,Fgo away?
